<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="246" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,793,1288]" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis box="[151,453,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Female pregenital segment</emphasis>
. Posterior margin of sternite VII conically produced medially, with median very narrow lightly sclerotized area in distal half, in basal region grooved, median projection slightly shorter than length of sternite preceding it; median area dark brown widening posteriorly, lateral angles slightly posteriorly produced (
<figureCitation box="[1302,1391,865,891]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,193,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4 A–G. Species of Drabescus from Indian subcontinent. D. stramineus Distant, lectotype female: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, face and thoracic sternites, ventral view; D, abdomen ventral view; E, data labels; F. Drabescus sp., nymph; G. D. limbaticephs (Stål), adult in natural habitat." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479824" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479824/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,793,1288]" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis box="[199,361,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Measurements</emphasis>
